rComments: He is an amazing professor. Very knowledgeable, helpful, understanding and caring. He is very funny and gives small extra grades for attending the lectures. He is easy to reach out to and always happy to help.

Guy just doesn't know what he's doing. He seems fun and energetic but his lectures are based off just reading slides and providing very little extra information. Would not recommend if you want to actually learn something.
Take any class with him. He cares about his students, makes materials accessible and is hilarious.
He's a funny prof and his course is pretty easy. Just make sure you go to class and participate for marks. He's willing to help with essays and help you get better.
He is amazing. Thats all. If you have a chance to take a course with him, DO IT. Unlike your usual stuck up UofT professor.
Amazing and engaging professor. He cares about his students a lot and gives us the chance to succeed in his classes. He was very approachable and offered bonus assignments to help boost our grades!

Took his course at UTSG. He's ok. We had an awful TA he kept on defending, which I found kind of annoying. He was usually helpful but he was not on the same page as the TA so his helpfulness was never really all that helpful? He's funny but sometimes I feel as though it's a cover up for how he doesn't know what he's doing. I guess he's trying...

Amazing prof, makes anything interesting and gets you to really think. The TA was a really hard marker but Tatham is great. Make sure you do the readings for the class though because he doesn't discuss readings in lecture, and you have to go to lecture because the slides arent enough, he gives lots of other info!!!
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read', 'Hilarious']

rComments: Solid prof. I found him hilarious
He's hilarious! He's very fun and while his course on white collar crime could be boring, he was always funny enough to make me keep going to lectures. He is a fair grader and was very approachable.

Prof Tatham has been one of my absolute favorite profs. He's so funny and chill. He understands that as students we have a lot going on so he is very accommodating, giving lots of opportunity for students to do well. He's super approachable and lectures are informative and interesting. He gives lots of interesting examples and cases.

The semester is still going on but I can honestly say he is one of the best professors I have ever had. He's absolutely hilarious, super approachable, and he really cares about his students. His lectures are easy to keep up with, and he always tries to make sure you get the most marks possible through things like kahoot and bonus questions on tests

Prof. Tatham is awesome. His lectures always include pictures and video examples that relate to course content. He is super approachable, very helpful both in and out of class. Holds extended office hours when needed and is very good with responding to emails

Tatham is the sweetest prof UTM has! He is seriously super cool and funny which makes his long lectures a lot easier to deal with. His tests are straight forward (BONUS MARKS)! If you go to lectures and take good notes, you will do extremely well in his course. Textbook and readings are not necessary. He is so caring and wants you to succeed.

I took SOC208&316 with Chris. Overall he's a great guy. His lectures are always entertaining and he gives great feedback for essays and tests. Tests are always straightforward and focus on the main points of the lecture. They are long/short answer so it gives you space to relay what you've learned and thankfully no multiple choice garbage.

This is an amazing Prof lectures are hilarious, and you learn a lot. The exam just asks a simple question on each reading to see if you actually read it. Don't hesitate to ask for help outside class it will really help and he is approachable and kind and cares tons
A great Professor. Funny, smart, just overall awesome. Take this class! if you attend lectures you can do really well.

I loved taking him in SOC208! He's really easy to understand. The lectures in the beginning are filled with information to get you introduced to the material. Then he slowly makes him less filled up, so he knows students are paying attention. He's so approachable, and he's willing to help. I love how he's easy-going. My favourite professor!

One of the best professors I have met, very genuine, cares for his students and super NICE!. He knows his stuff well and which helps alot. Very funny while teaching thus making it a perfect learning experience. Will take him again anytime!

Tatham is such a funny and warm-hearted individual. He really cares about his students and does a great job at making his lectures interesting. His Kahoot participation is genius and he makes me actually want to come to class. He is very knowledgeable and brings life to course content. His life digressions are very entertaining! Give him tenure!

Honestly a really nice prof. I would definetely recommend him and will try my best to take classes with him in teh future.  Hes also very sympathetic. It sucked that some people bought teh textbook considering we only read 5 chapters from it, but i guess taht was their loss. i never bought teh textbook nor did teh readings and did good. :)
Love love this prof! His midterms are straightforward and his lectures are interesting and fun. 4.0 is obtainable, just study well and ask the prof for help

Professor Tatham was very passionate about the course and was very thorough in his lectures. Although they were long lectures, they definitely were not boring with his videos and sense of humour. I am a first year student that did not find this second year class as challenging as I thought it would be, which is a good thing. He is super helpful too

Tatham is a precious cinnamon roll of a human being and must be protected at all costs. Seriously he's amazing, so sweet and genuine. Wants the best for his students and is passionate about what he teaches. Excellent prof if you wanna be comforted by the fact that he's always there for you and wants to help you succeed.

The best prof I've had in my entire undergrad, SO KIND, SO UNDERSTANDING! Really cares about students doing well so he'll just give u free partcipation/bonus marks on tests to help u (even when u didn't do the bonus q). Has fun videos/documentaries for lectures on organized crime/mobs etc, and he goes out of his way to help ppl with their papers!
He tries to help you in any way possible if you come to him for help. he truly wants to see his students succeed. great guy!

Easy MC midterm. Final had short answer questions that were vague and very hard to answer clearly. He basically asked us to summarize what we knew about each chapter. Nevertheless, he's a pretty cool guy and a fair marker.
Nicest prof I've ever had.
Fun class. Good prof.
